C

Cell - Class in Maze
Cell class which describes a cell object that contains a north, east, south, and west wall as well as information that describes whether it is a cell that is visible, visited, or it's type (border, time point, end point, etc...).
Cell(int) - Constructor for class Maze.Cell
Initializes this cell object where each wall in the cell is existent.
cellBox - Variable in class Maze.RectCell
Rectangle object representing the cell tile.
cellColor - Variable in class Maze.GraphicsMaze
Default cell tile color if tile is not a start, end or time point cell.
cellNumber - Variable in class Maze.Cell
Represents the cell number based on the dimensions of the maze (i.e., 2 by 2 maze has 1 to 4 cell numbers).
Character - Class in Maze
Character class which contains information on how a character object (player) should behave; handles movement upon input, collisions and redraw functions.
Character(int, int, GraphicsMaze) - Constructor for class Maze.Character
Initializes the initial x and y position of the character object, the speed and the dimensions (size of player).
collide(String) - Method in class Maze.Character
Collision detection/avoidance, projects a copy of the character object to a new position corresponding to the direction "direc" and then checks if a collision will occur at that point before moving the player.
colMaze - Variable in class Maze.Character
Graphics Maze object used to obtain a clone of the current maze drawn in order for correct collision detection.
columnCounter - Variable in class Maze.GamePanel
Column counter value which is adjusted (determines next column value) to move to the next cell in order to hide cells in the end game animation.
coordX - Variable in class Maze.Cell
Represents the physical x coordinate of this cell object on the maze (Graphical maze).
coordY - Variable in class Maze.Cell
Represents the physical y coordinate of this cell object on the maze (Graphical maze).
copy - Static variable in class Maze.GraphicsMaze
Thread safe array list of RectCell objects used for cloning and collision detection.
